{
  "texts": [
    "Various other ways to obtain fixed-size images have been proposed.",
    "In the method proposed by Ho et al. (2018), a fixed input image size was chosen and the images were either cropped or padded with zeros to adjust them to the correct size.",
    "Schröder et al. (2018) proposed to crop the images to their tight bounding box and pad to a square with a minimum edge length of 128 pixels.",
    "Images larger than 128 pixels were shrunken to the same size.",
    "Ellen et al. (2019) resized images larger than the target size thus losing some detail."
  ]
}